  • Teri Olsen
    5.0 out of 5 starsAmazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product
    Versatile Dust Cover – Even For Old Computer Monitors!
    Reviewed in the United States on August 19, 2024
    The MozkeTo19 dust cover is designed with air fryers, toaster ovens, and convection ovens in mind, but it will fit over anything that’s about 17” square x 16” high. I have a vintage computer monitor, the old CRT kind. I wanted to protect it from dust but of course you can’t... See more
    The MozkeTo19 dust cover is designed with air fryers, toaster ovens, and convection ovens in mind, but it will fit over anything that’s about 17” square x 16” high. I have a vintage computer monitor, the old CRT kind. I wanted to protect it from dust but of course you can’t find dust covers of that size anymore. I happened to see this item and the dimensions were pretty much just what I needed. The black nylon fabric had a weird fishy smell when I first got it out of the package but it’s fine now. More importantly, it fits almost perfectly! It was about an inch too tall but I just folded the bottom hem over by that much and it stays in place well. I didn’t need to use the drawstring. This cover is great because it has a handle on top so you can simply lift it up to take it off. It’s sturdy and keeps its square shape without being floppy. The package includes two scratch-free wire cleaning cloths, which will be handy in the kitchen for wiping off baked on grease and grime. I’m so glad I came across this product!

    Nice toaster oven cover but bad smell!
    Reviewed in the United States on August 18, 2024
    This is such a nice toaster oven cover but bad smell! I really enjoy this appliance cover it fits my toaster oven perfectly and protects it from scratches and dust while not in use. However I would recommend opening and letting the cover air out outside or in your garage... See more
    This is such a nice toaster oven cover but bad smell! I really enjoy this appliance cover it fits my toaster oven perfectly and protects it from scratches and dust while not in use. However I would recommend opening and letting the cover air out outside or in your garage due to the bad chemical smell. I let the cover air out in my garage overnight and it was fine to bring in the house. I really like the bottom drawstring to help keep the appliance cover securely on your appliance. The material seems durable and the construction is done very well. I would still recommend this nice toaster oven cover but please note the bad smell!
